1. Package Download. 
- Login to the server and download all the required Packages.
wget https://dlcdn.apache.org/httpd/httpd-2.4.62.tar.bz2
wget https://github.com/PCRE2Project/pcre2/releases/download/pcre2-10.44/pcre2-10.44.tar.bz2
wget https://dlcdn.apache.org/apr/apr-util-1.6.3.tar.bz2
wget https://dlcdn.apache.org/apr/apr-1.7.5.tar.bz2

2. Extract the downloaded files. 
- Extract all the directories.
tar -xjf apr-1.7.5.tar.bz2
tar -xjf apr-util-1.6.3.tar.bz2
tar -xjf httpd-2.4.62.tar.bz2
tar -xjf pcre2-10.44.tar.bz2


3. Apache Configuration. 
- For manual installation need to configure all the packages. In the below order.
Note: In Prefix we mention the path in which we want apache to be configured.
•	For APR Package
cd apr-1.7.5/
./configure --prefix=/opt/apache2/apr
make
make install
•	For APR-UTIL Package
cd apr-util-1.6.3/
./configure --prefix=/opt/apache2/apr-util --with-apr=/opt/apache2/apr
make
make install
•	For PCRE Package
cd pcre2-10.44/
./configure --prefix=/opt/apache2/pcre
make
make install
•	For HTTPD Package
cd httpd-2.4.62/
./configure --prefix=/opt/apache2/ --with-apr=/opt/apache2/apr --with-apr-util=/opt/apache2/apr-util --with-pcre=/opt/apache2/pcre/bin/pcre2-config
make
make install
3. Creation of Service File. 
- Service file should be created for gracefully auto start and stop of the apache2 service. 
•	The file has been created in /opt/service_files/ directory.
vim /opt/service_files/apache2.service

[Unit]
Description=The Apache HTTP Server
After=network.target opt.mount
Requires=opt.mount

[Service]
Type=forking
ExecStart=/opt/apache2/bin/apachectl start
ExecReload=/opt/apache2/bin/apachectl graceful
ExecStop=/opt/apache2/bin/apachectl stop
PIDFile=/opt/apache2/logs/httpd.pid
PrivateTmp=true

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
•	A softlink has been created in /etc/systemd/system/. 
cd /etc/systemd/system 
ln -s /opt/service_files/apache2.service
•	Start and enable the service file.
systemctl enable apache2.service
systemctl start apache2.service
systemctl status apache2.service

4. Updating the httpd.conf file 
•	Create a directory in /opt/apache2/conf/virtual_hosts/ and create all the virtual hosts files in it. This will help to manage the configuration files.
•	Update the below lines in httpd.conf file.
# Virtual hosts
Include conf/virtual_hosts/*.conf

Enter On last Line
Servername localhost

•	Restart the apache2 service.
